Oliver Cromwell]\n* [https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0065593/ Cromwell (1970)] at [[Internet Movie Database|IMDb]]\n\n{{-}}\n{{S-start}}\n{{s-par|en}}\n|-\n{{s-bef|before = [[Arthur Mainwaring]]|before2 = John Goldsborough}} \n{{s-ttl|title = Member of Parliament for [[Huntingdon (UK Parliament constituency)|Huntingdon]]|years = 1628\u20131629|with = James Montagu}} \n{{s-vac|reason= Parliament suspended until 1640|next=[[Sir Robert Bernard, 1st Baronet|Robert Bernard]]|next2=[[William Montagu (judge)|William Montagu]]}}\n|-\n{{s-vac|reason= Parliament suspended since 1629|last=Thomas Purchase}} \n{{s-ttl|title = Member of Parliament for [[Cambridge (UK Parliament constituency)|Cambridge]]|years = 1640\u20131653|with = [[Thomas Meautys]] 1640|with2 = [[John Lowry (Parliamentarian)|John Lowry]] 1640\u20131653}} \n{{s-vac|reason = Not represented in Barebones Parliament|next=Richard Timbs}} \n|- \n{{s-mil}}\n{{s-bef|before= [[Thomas Fairfax]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title= [[Commander-in-Chief of the Forces|Captain General and Commander-in-Chief of the Forces]] |years=1650\u20131653}}\n{{s-vac|reason=Cromwell elected [[Lord Protector]]|next=  [[George Monck, 1st Duke of Albemarle|George Monck]]}}   \n{{S-off}}\n|-\n{{s-non|reason= [[English Council of State|Council of State]]}} \n{{s-ttl|title = [[Lord Protector of England, Scotland and Ireland]]|years = 16 December 1653 \u2013 3 September 1658}} \n{{s-aft|after = [[Richard Cromwell]]}} \n{{S-aca}}\n{{s-bef|before = [[Philip Herbert, 4th Earl of Pembroke|Earl of Pembroke]]}} \n{{s-ttl|title = [[List of Chancellors of the University of Oxford|Chancellor of the University of Oxford]]|years = 1650\u20131653}} \n{{s-aft|after = [[Richard Cromwell]]}}\n{{S-end}}\n{{English monarchs}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cromwell, Oliver}}\n[[Category:Oliver Cromwell| ]]\n[[Category:1599 births]]\n[[Category:1658 deaths]]\n[[Category:17th-century English Puritans]]\n[[Category:Alumni of Sidney Sussex College, Cambridge]]\n[[Category:A