duced '''39''' All-American players, as well as '''6''' Academic All-Americans.  Since Troy joined the [[National Collegiate Athletic Association|NCAA]]'s Division I in 1994, the program has had '''16''' players named as All-Americans.\n\nThe following is a list of all '''First Team All-Americans''' Troy has had since joining Division I:\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"background:white;\n|-\n! style=\"background: #8e0028; color:white;|Player\n! style=\"background: #8e0028; color:white;|Position\n! style=\"background: #8e0028; color:white;|Year(s)\n! style=\"background: #8e0028; color:white;|Selectors\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| Nate Moore\n| [[Pitcher|P]]\n| [[2004 College Baseball All-America Team|2004]]\n| ''Baseball America''\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| Tom King\n| [[Shortstop|SS]]\n| [[2006 College Baseball All-America Team|2006]]\n| ''Collegaite Baseball'', NCBWA, Louisville Slugger\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| Bryan Miller\n| [[Outfielder|OF]]\n| [[2008 College Baseball All-America Team|2008]]\n| ''Collegiate Baseball''\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| Adam Bryant\n| [[Shortstop|SS]]\n| [[2010 College Baseball All-America Team|2010]]\n| Ping!Baseball.com\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| Tyler Hannah\n| [[Third Baseman|3B]]\n| [[2011 College Baseball All-America Team|2011]]\n| ''Collegiate Baseball''\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| Danny Collins\n| [[Outfielder|OF]]\n| [[2013 College Baseball All-America Team|2013]]\n| ''Collegiate Baseball'', NCBWA\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|}\n\n==Award Winners/Finalists==\n*'''[[American Baseball Coaches Association|ABCA]] National Coach of the Year\n:[[Chase Riddle]] \u2013 1986, 1987\n:John Mayotte \u2013 1993\n\n*'''[[American Baseball Coaches Association|Rawlings Gold Glove Award]]'''\n:Brett Henry \u2013 2009\n:Brandon Lockridge \u2013 2018\n\n*'''[[Brooks Wallace Award]] Finalist'''\n:Adam Bryant \u2013 2010\n:Tyler Vaughn \u2013 2013\n\n==MLB Draft==\nTroy has had '''59''' total players selected in the [[MLB Draft]] in its history.  Click the \"show\" button at the top corner of the table below in order to see the list of Trojans that have been drafted.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable collapsible collapsed\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! colspan=4 style=\"background:#8e0028; color:#FFFFFF\" |Trojans in the Major League Baseball Draft\n|-\n! Year\n! Player\n! Round\n! Team\n|-\n| [[1967 Major League Baseball draft|1967]]\n|{{sort name|Wesley|Rutledge|nolink=1}}\n| 20\n| [[St. Louis Cardinals|St. Louis]]\n|-\n| [[1977 Major League Baseball draft|1977]]\n|{{sort name|Ronnie|Reasoner|nolink=1}}\n| 28\n| [[Detroit Tigers|Detroit]]\n|-\n| [[1978 Major League Baseball draft|1978]]\n|{{sort name|Kenneth|Gilmore|nolink=1}}\n| 27\n| [[Cleveland Indians|Cleveland]]\n|-\n| [[1979 Major League Baseball draft|1979]]\n|{{sort name|Stan|McCauley|nolink=1}}\n| 26\n| [[St. Louis Cardinals|St. Louis]]\n|-\n| [[1981 Major League Baseball draft|1981]]\n|{{sort name|Danny|Cox|Danny Cox (baseball)}}\n| 13\n| [[St. Louis Cardinals|St. Louis]]\n|-\n| [[1981 Major League Baseball draft|1981]]\n|{{sort name|Kevin|McDaniel|nolink=1}}\n| 32\n| [[Montreal Expos|Montreal]]\n|-\n| [[1982 Major League Baseball draft|1982]]\n|{{sort name|Pedro|LaTorre|nolink=1}}\n| 14\n| [[St. Louis Cardinals|St. Louis]]\n|-\n| [[1985 Major League Baseball draft|1985]]\n|{{sort name|David|Banks|nolink=1}}\n| 25\n| [[New York Yankees|New York (AL)]]\n|-\n| [[1985 Major League Baseball draft|1985]]\n|{{sort name|Ray|Stephens|nolink=1}}\n| 6\n| [[St. Louis Cardinals|St. Louis]]\n|-\n| [[1985 Major League Baseball draft|1985]]\n|{{sort name|Chuck|Stanhope|nolink=1}}\n| 6\n| [[Baltimore Orioles|Baltimore]]\n|-\n| [[1985 Major League Baseball draft|1985]]\n|{{sort name|Buck|Watford|nolink=1}}\n| 14\n| [[Toronto Blue Jays|Toronto]]\n|-\n| [[1986 Major League Baseball draft|1986]]\n|{{sort name|Vince|Kindred|nolink=1}}\n| 7\n| [[St. Louis Cardinals|St. Louis]]\n|-\n| [[1986 Major League Baseb