ida Marlins|Florida]]\n|-\n| [[1996 Major League Baseball draft|1996]]\n|{{sort name|Duane|Eason|nolink=1}}\n| 48\n| [[Pittsburgh Pirates|Pittsburgh]]\n|-\n| [[1997 Major League Baseball draft|1997]]\n|{{sort name|Ryan|Pearson|nolink=1}}\n| 43\n| [[Milwaukee Brewers|Milwaukee]]\n|-\n| [[1999 Major League Baseball draft|1999]]\n|{{sort name|Jorge|Soto|nolink=1}}\n| 3\n| [[Oakland Athletics|Oakland]]\n|-\n| [[1999 Major League Baseball draft|1999]]\n|{{sort name|Casey|Williamson|nolink=1}}\n| 19\n| [[Detroit Tigers|Detroit]]\n|-\n| [[1999 Major League Baseball draft|1999]]\n|{{sort name|Kevan|Burns|nolink=1}}\n| 26\n| [[Arizona Diamondbacks|Arizona]]\n|-\n| [[1999 Major League Baseball draft|1999]]\n|{{sort name|Tom|Gregorio|nolink=1}}\n| 27\n| [[Los Angeles Angels|Los Angeles (AL)]]\n|-\n| [[2001 Major League Baseball draft|2001]]\n|{{sort name|Casey|Smith|nolink=1}}\n| 34\n| [[Los Angeles Angels|Los Angeles (AL)]]\n|-\n| [[2001 Major League Baseball draft|2001]]\n|{{sort name|Jason|Bernard|nolink=1}}\n| 27\n| [[Philadelphia Phillies|Philadelphia]]\n|-\n| [[2004 Major League Baseball draft|2004]]\n|{{sort name|Nate|Moore|nolink=1}}\n| 4\n| [[Kansas City Royals|Kansas City]]\n|-\n| [[2004 Major League Baseball draft|2004]]\n|{{sort name|Todd|Nicholas|nolink=1}}\n| 36\n| [[Montreal Expos|Montreal]]\n|-\n| [[2005 Major League Baseball draft|2005]]\n|{{sort name|Adam|Godwin|nolink=1}}\n| 11\n| [[Los Angeles Dodgers|Los Angeles (NL)]]\n|-\n| [[2005 Major League Baseball draft|2005]]\n|{{sort name|Henry|Gutierrez|nolink=1}}\n| 11\n| [[San Francisco Giants|San Francisco]]\n|-\n| [[2006 Major League Baseball draft|2006]]\n|{{sort name|Mike|Felix|nolink=1}}\n| 2\n| [[Pittsburgh Pirates|Pittsburgh]]\n|-\n| [[2006 Major League Baseball draft|2006]]\n|{{sort name|Tom|King|nolink=1}}\n| 8\n| [[San Diego Padres|San Diego]]\n|-\n| [[2006 Major League Baseball draft|2006]]\n|{{sort name|Jarred|Keel|nolink=1}}\n| 31\n| [[Pittsburgh Pirates|Pittsburgh]]\n|-\n| [[2007 Major League Base