Mariners|Seattle]]\n|}\n\n==Notable Alumni==\n[[File:Fred Hatfield 1953.jpg|180px|right|thumb|[[Fred Hatfield|Fred \"Scrap Iron\" Hatfield]] with the [[Detroit Tigers]] in 1953.]]\n\nThe following players made their way onto Major League rosters from either being drafted or signed as free agents:\n\n{{Div col|colwidth=40em}}\n*[[Clint Robinson (baseball)|Clint Robinson]]\n*[[Chase Whitley]]\n*[[Fred Hatfield|Fred \"Scrap Iron\" Hatfield]]\n*[[Mackey Sasser]]\n*[[Danny Cox (baseball)|Danny Cox]]\n*[[TJ Rivera]]\n*[[Mike Rivera (baseball)|Mike Rivera]]\n*[[Tom Drake (baseball)|Tom Drake]]\n*[[Danny Breeden]]\n*[[Mike P\u00e9rez (baseball)|Mike P\u00e9rez]]\n*[[Ray Stephens]]\n*[[Tom Gregorio]]\n*[[Grady Wilson (baseball)|Grady Wilson]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Championships==\n[[Image:Riddle Pace Field Plaza 3.jpg|250px|thumb|right|Troy's Baseball Hall of Fame & Championships wall, located in the main concourse beneath the stadium.]]\n\nSince Troy's first year in [[NCAA Division I|Division I]] in 1994, the program has won six regular-season conference titles and three conference tournament titles.\n\nIn the team's short stint in the Mid-Continent Conference, they won the regular season title in three straight seasons, from 1995 to 1997, to go along with two tournament titles in 1995 and 1997.  In Troy's last season in the [[Atlantic Sun Conference]] in 2005, they won the regular season title.  Since joining the [[Sun Belt Conference]], the team has won three regular season titles in 2006, 2011, and 2013.  Troy also won the SBC tournament title in 2006.\n\nThe program has compiled a total of 20 conference championships and two [[NCAA Division II|D-II]] national championships since its inception.\n\n===Conference Season Championships===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n{{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=Troy Trojans|Year|Coach|Record|Conference Title}}\n| 1980 || [[Chase Riddle]] || 30\u201312 (12\u20132) || [[Gulf South Conference]] Champions\n|-\n| 1981 || Chase Riddle || 37\u201310 (12\u20130) || [[Gulf South Conference]] Champions\n|-\n| 1982 || Chase Riddle || 31\u201310 (8\u20133) || [[Gulf South Conference]] Champions\n|-\n| 1986 || Chase Riddle || 46\u20138 (12\u20130) || [[Gulf South Conference]] Champions\n|-\n| 1989 || Chase Riddle || 29\u201316 (6\u20138) || [[Gulf South Conference]] Champions\n|-\n| 1996 || John Mayotte || 41\u201313 (18\u20132) || [[The Summit League|Mid-Continent Conference]] Champions\n|-\n| 1997 || John Mayotte || 37\u201323 (8\u20136) || [[The Summit League|Mid-Continent Conference]] Champions\n|-\n| 2005 || [[Bobby Pierce]] || 37\u201321 (23\u20137) || [[Atlantic Sun Conference]] Champions\n|-  \n| 2006 || Bobby Pierce || 47\u201316 (20\u20134) || [[Sun Belt Conference]] Champions\n|-\n| 2011 || Bobby Pierce || 43\u201319 (21\u20139) || [[Sun Belt Conference]] Champions\n|-\n| 2013 || Bobby Pierce || 42\u201320 (20\u201310) || [[Sun Belt Conference]] Champions\n|- style=\"{{NCAA secondary color cell|Troy Trojans}}; font-weight:bold;\"\n| colspan=3| Regular Season championships:\n| 11\n|}\n\n===Conference Tournament Championships===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n{{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=Troy Trojans|Year|Coach|Record|Conference Title}}\n| 1980 || [[Chase Riddle]] || 30\u201312 (12\u20132) || [[Gulf South Conference]] Champions\n|-\n| 1981 || Chase Riddle || 37\u201310 (12\u20130) || [[Gulf South Conference]] Champions\n|-\n| 1982 || Chase Riddle || 31\u201310 (8\u20133) || [[Gulf South Conference]] Champions\n|-\n| 1986 || Chase Riddle || 46\u20138 (12\u20130) || [[Gulf South Conference]] Champions\n|-\n| 1987 || Chase Riddle || 38\u201310\u20131 (8\u20135) || [[Gulf South Conference]] Champions\n|-\n| 1990 || Chase Riddle || 50\u201310 (9\u20133) || [[Gulf South Conference]] Champions\n|-\n| 1995 || John Mayotte || 41\u201313 (18\u20132) || [[The Summit League|Mid-Continent Conference]] Champions\n|-\n| 1997 || John Mayotte || 37\u201323 (8\u20136)